  "verificationNotes": "Existence, 3.8B params, MIT license, April 23 2024 Azure launch all confirmed. CORRECTED ctxK from 128 to 4: the record's own hf link names the '4k' variant (microsoft/Phi-3-mini-4k-instruct), and that model card / the original Phi-3 Technical Report confirm a native 4096-token context window (128K belongs to the separate sibling microsoft/Phi-3-mini-128k-instruct) \u2014 kept the record scoped to the 4k-instruct card per its own hf link. Fetched the live HF model card and confirmed all 5 benchmark rows verbatim (MMLU 70.9, HumanEval 57.3, GSM8K 85.7, BBH 73.5, GPQA 30.6); note these are the card's 'June 2024 Update' numbers superseding the original April 2024 launch table in the arXiv report (MMLU 68.8, GPQA 23.7) \u2014 both are legitimately Microsoft-reported for this same model, just at different checkpoints, and the record's numbers match the current/live card. Azure AI Foundry price ($0.13/$0.52 per 1M tokens) could not be independently reconfirmed on the current pricing page (fetch timed out) but no contradicting figure was found either; left as reported."
